  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>The Discount Report shows all discounts applied to your ticket items. We recommend accounting based on closed tickets only; once a ticket is closed the date will no longer change, and the sales are reported as revenue. By default, filters are set to closed tickets, because it is the most reliable method for this business model. For further information about accrual-based reporting, see our article, <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934360642\" rel=\"nofollow\">RepairQ Accounting Principles</a>.</p><h3 id=\"Reports:DiscountsSummaryandDiscountsDetail-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/2094923832\" rel=\"nofollow\">Discounts: Activation and General Settings</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/2095546399\" rel=\"nofollow\">Discounts: Creation and Customization</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/2098036767\" rel=\"nofollow\">Discount Management on Tickets</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934360642\" rel=\"nofollow\">RepairQ Accounting Principles</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2098069535/Technical%20-%20124a6d.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Reports:DiscountsSummaryandDiscountsDetail-ViewDiscountReporting\">View Discount Reporting</h2><p>On the Navigation Bar, click <strong>Reports</strong>. On the Reports page, click the <strong>Returns &amp; Adjustments dropdown</strong> to expand available reports. From the list click <strong>Discounts Summary </strong>or <strong>Discounts Detail</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2098069535/Discount%20Report%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2098069535/Discount%20Report%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Use the available filters to scope results based on the assigned parameters. Once you have made your selections, click <strong>Apply Filters </strong>to run the report.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Date Range </strong>- Select a date range for your scope of results.</p></li><li><p><strong>Ticket Status </strong>- Choose to view results based on ticket status. By default, the report will run for tickets in Closed status, since ticket information is finalized.</p></li><li><p><strong>Location </strong>- Select a specific location or an aggregate report for multiple/all locations.</p></li><li><p><strong>Discount </strong>- Select a specific discount or an aggregate report for multiple/all discounts applied on a ticket.</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2098069535/Discount%20Report%203.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"Reports:DiscountsSummaryandDiscountsDetail-ExportingtheReport\">Exporting the Report</h3><p>On the upper-right corner of the page, you can switch between Summary and Detail reporting, Export to Excel,\u00a0and\u00a0Hide/Show Filters from the report view. The export will include data matching your filtered results.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"368\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2098069535/Discount%20Report%204.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Reports:DiscountsSummaryandDiscountsDetail-DiscountSummary\">Discount Summary</h2><p>The Discount Summary Report gives you a broad summary of discounts applied to each Item Type. This report also includes total discounts for each type, discounts returned, and net discounts.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2098069535/Discount%20Report%205.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Reports:DiscountsSummaryandDiscountsDetail-DiscountDetail\">Discount Detail</h2><p>The Discount Detail Report list tickets with columns that detail Date/Time, Catalog Item, Discount Name, and sales details. There are also links to view the ticket and Inventory Item Summary. </p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2098069535/Discount%20Report%206.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p><p />",
